The paper deals with the problem of verifying privacy guarantees of algorithms, which is a central concern in the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The lower bounds on query complexity suggest that the paper also involves computational complexity and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of differential privacy is a key topic in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG), and the paper specifically deals with verifying different types of differential privacy guarantees. The use of algorithms and complexity theory in the paper suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
